"A dozen or so cases [ of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid ] will be gone in half an hour! "

On February 1, Soulain (not his real name) , a pharmacy worker at a Sanjia hospital in Henan Province, told the Beijing News that the hospital had only prescribed Shuanghuanglian oral solution for fever clinics because of a shortage of Shuanghuanglian.

Meanwhile, a manufacturer of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid as far away as Dongguan has been told by the Dongguan municipal government to step up production of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid, "starting production today" .

Shuanghuanglian oral liquid became in short supply overnight, in connection with a study released on the evening of January 31 by the Shanghai Institute of Medicine of the Chinese Academy of Sciences and the Wuhan Institute of Virology: "Preliminary findings suggest that the Chinese Patent Medicine Shuanghuanglian oral liquid can inhibit COVID-19. " Subsequently, the major e-commerce platform of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid and other products were snapped up.

Modern Medical Research has concluded that Shuanghuanglian oral liquid is one of the most effective broad-spectrum drugs with broad-spectrum antiviral, bacteriostatic and enhancing immune functions, according to a message forwarded by Government of the People's Republic of China in the early morning. Antiviral drug. "At present, Shuanghuanglian oral liquid has been studied in Shanghai Public Health Clinical Center and Huazhong University of Science and Technology Affiliated Tongji Hospital. "

But can Shuanghuanglian oral liquid really suppress COVID-19? Experts and medical experts have questioned whether there is enough public data to prove that it "suppresses COVID-19" in humans.

Shuanghuanglian oral liquid "inhibition of coronavirus" ? There's a limited prescription at the hospital

Early in the morning of February 1, Soulain (not his real name) , who works in the pharmacy of a Sanjia hospital in a city in Henan Province, received a call from the director of the warehouse to leave a box of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid, "Hurry up and report the double yellow line plan, line up to buy" .

A colleague on duty told Soulain that a patient came to buy double Coptis last night, but it was out of stock, let the other side in the morning to buy. "about a dozen cases went missing in half an hour, " Soulain told reporters.

Shuanghuanglian sold out, and Soulain immediately contacted the hospital for purchase. "The pharmaceutical company said that someone would come at 2:00 in the morning and ask for the goods. Now we can only begin to distribute them. Each hospital can distribute a little bit. It can not be said that whoever preempts it first is the one who gets it. " "The final pharmaceutical department notice can only fever clinic prescription (Shuanghuanglian oral liquid) , up to 7 days of volume. ".

Soulain advised the public, do not line up at the hospital to buy Shuanghuanglian oral liquid, "hospital suspected cases, to the hospital is not safe. ".

"A preliminary study found that Shuanghuanglian oral liquid, a Chinese patent medicine, can inhibit COVID-19, " the Shanghai Institute of Medicine and Wuhan Institute of Virology of the Chinese Academy of Sciences announced on the evening of January 31, hSINKING newspaper reporters looked at Taobao, jd.com, suning e-commerce platform found that most of the goods show no goods or off the shelf.

But can Shuanghuanglian oral liquid really suppress COVID-19? Some medical experts have a different view.

On February 1st Dr Clove wrote that animal trials, Phase I trials, Phase II trials and Phase III trials are needed to prove that a drug works. "At present, Shuanghuanglian oral liquid has been studied in Shanghai Public Health Clinical Center and Tongji Hospital affiliated to the Huazhong University of Science and Technology, " the Shanghai Institute of Medicine and Wuhan Institute of Virology said, there's not enough public data to prove it's COVID-19 in humans.

"inhibition is not equal to prevention and treatment, " the People's Daily said in a microblog post on the morning of Feb. 1. According to the World Health Organization, "to date, there are no drugs to prevent or treat COVID-19. ".

People in Shanghai snapped up Shuanghuanglian oral liquid in the middle of the night, which was sold out by drug store workers. Beijing News Our video production (ID: Wevideo)

In a frenzy of demand, some factories are expanding production at the government's request

After the announcement of "Shuanghuanglian oral liquid can inhibit COVID-19" , what is the situation of the major pharmaceutical factories of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid?

"The orders are very large, " Huang Yuzhu, chief engineer of Harbin No. 4 Factory of Traditional Chinese medicine, told the Beijing News on Feb. 1. "Many companies want as many as they have. ".

Huang said that the fourth factory of Harbin's traditional Chinese medicine started producing Shuanghuanglian oral liquid ahead of schedule on the second day of the Lunar New Year. The factory now has an annual production capacity of 70 to 80 million units, and the production cycle of the oral liquid is long, and "it may take half a month from the extraction of raw materials to the factory, " she said.

In the last 3 days or so, Harbin No. 4 Chinese Medicine Factory has received orders for Shuanghuanglian oral liquid from some companies. "It is a traditional formula, aimed at clearing away heat and detoxifying, among which honeysuckle also has anti-inflammatory effect. ". For the effectiveness of the Suppression of COVID-19, Huang Yuzhu that "the specific need for experimental data" , "in the current epidemic situation, at least on the heat and anti-inflammatory effect is useful. ".

"At present, the government may also focus on purchasing. The Harbin New District government and the provincial drug administration have also been paying attention to our production capacity recently. They need to understand the situation and may have a consideration on the follow-up of the overall drug allocation, " said Huang Yuzhu.

Chinese medicine companies respond to double RHIZOMA COPTIDIS inhibition of new coronavirus: the second day of the Lunar New Year began to work overtime. Beijing News Video Production (ID: Wevideo)

When a reporter from the Beijing News called Fusen Pharmaceutical on Feb. 1, a marketing department official responded that the company was already ramping up production. "We have already communicated with the government, and I'm not sure how. ". Another staff member told reporters that the company probably began to work overtime production from the second and third day of the eighth lunar month, under the full load condition, the first two years of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid annual production capacity reached 1 billion.

On Feb. 1, the Beijing News contacted the Heilongjiang-based Reger Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. . The company's staff told the reporter that the current epidemic is serious, the only thing the company can do is normal production, and there is no overtime production, "We are now out of stock in some markets and are anxious to deliver the goods, but production is limited, we do not want to expand, and we can not increase production without relevant approval. " "If produced all year round, Shuanghuanglian oral liquid could produce 100 to 150 million doses, "

Unlike the two companies, staff at Dongguan Pharmaceutical Co Ltd in Guangdong told the reporter that the company's maximum annual production of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid is about 500 million sticks, mainly sold in Guangdong, at present has received the Dongguan municipal government to increase the production of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid notice. "normal production started today and the [ Dongguan ] government didn't start requiring us until after the announcement of the Shanghai Institute of Medicine yesterday, " the official said.

"Shuanghuanglian" related drug batch number 85, of which 13 products for oral liquid

According to a search on the website of the Hsinking State Food and Drug Administration, there are 85 products related to Shuanghuanglian, 13 of which are Shuanghuanglian oral liquid, the rest are Shuanghuanglian tablets, Shuanghuanglian suppository, Shuanghuanglian capsules, Shuanghuanglian granules, Shuanghuanglian Syrup, Shuanghuanglian dropping pills, Shuanghuanglian tablets, Shuanghuanglian injection, Shuanghuanglian effervescent tablets and other products.

A search by a Hsinking newspaper reporter on the State Food and Drug Administration of chinese-made drugs found that there are currently 12 enterprises with 13 batch numbers that have been approved for the production of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid, they are: Heilongjiang Ruige Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. , Henan Tailong Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. (Z41020565 for Sinopharm and Z20133010 for Sinopharm) , Heilongjiang Linbao Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. , Dongguan Asia Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. , Harbin Pharmaceutical Group Sanjing Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. , Nanyang Xinsheng Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. , Jinjiu Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. , Henan Fusen Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. , Henan Tiandi Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. , Harbin No. 4 Chinese Medicine Factory Co. , Heilongjiang Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. and Zhenbao Island Pharmaceutical Group Co. , Ltd. .

Among the above-mentioned companies, Henan Tailong Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. and Heilongjiang Zhenbao Island Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. are all a-share listed companies, and Harbin Pharmaceutical Group Sanjing Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Harbin Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. , henan Tiandi Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. is a subsidiary of Tianshili Holding Company and Henan Fusen Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. is a listed company in Hong Kong stock market.

In the introduction of Tailong Pharmaceutical, Shuanghuanglian oral liquid for the main function of "wind, heat and detoxification. For the cold caused by exogenous wind and heat, symptoms see fever, cough, sore throat. "

In 2018, Tai Long Pharmaceutical produced 76.22 million doses of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid, 42.5224 million doses of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid (concentrated type) and 51.86 million doses of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid (children type) .

In 2018,191.46 million doses of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid were produced by Harbin Pharmaceutical Co. , according to the 2018 annual report of Harbin Pharmaceutical Co. .

On January 23, Harbin Pharmaceutical Group, in cooperation with Kyushu Tong, donated 10 million yuan worth of medicines to the Red Cross Society of Hubei Province through the Heilongjiang Cross Society, according to the Harbin Pharmaceutical Group's website, including Sanjing Brand Shuanghuanglian oral liquid, Shiyitang brand compound honeysuckle granules and so on.

Another Henan Fusen Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. announced on its official website at noon on January 31 that the company has made an emergency deployment of employees during the Spring Festival holiday, mobilized all internal resources, actively organized production, and all production lines are working at full capacity, work overtime to ensure product quality and production supply, as far as possible to meet market demand. At the same time, priority to the supply of goods security to the affected areas.

"SHUANGHUANGLIAN ANTI-NEW PNEUMONIA" without human testing, experts: caution

Can Shuanghuanglian oral liquid and other traditional Chinese medicines really prevent new coronavirus infection? Jinrui, deputy director of Beijing Shijitan Hospital, said that Shuanghuanglian oral liquid consists of honeysuckle, radix scutellariae and Fructus Forsythiae, which have good effects of clearing away heat and detoxication, and clearing both exterior and interior.

Modern medical research believes that Shuanghuanglian oral liquid has broad-spectrum antiviral, antibacterial, enhancing the body's immune function, is one of the effective broad-spectrum antiviral drug. "Shuanghuanglian oral liquid can inhibit COVID-19" is an in vitro study conducted from the perspective of virus inhibition in modern medicine, not according to the theory of traditional Chinese medicine. "from the perspective of Shuanghuanglian oral liquid itself, it can be considered as a bitter-cold medicine for clearing away heat and detoxifying. Some Chinese medicine academicians who attended the treatment in Wuhan suggested that bitter-cold medicine should be used with caution. " Jin Rui pointed out that Shuanghuanglian oral liquid was used as a proprietary Chinese medicine, the study should be conducted under the guidance of TCM theory. It is not suggested that normal people should take Shuanghuanglian oral liquid to prevent new coronavirus.

An unnamed pharmacist at a Sanjia hospital said that Shuanghuanglian oral liquid itself has broad-spectrum antiviral effect, but there are few studies on whether it is effective in inhibiting the new coronavirus, and no human trials, many drugs are effective in vitro but may not be effective in humans.

Jin Rui said that in the Chinese Medicine Treatment Plan of the fourth edition of the new coronavirus diagnosis and treatment plan released by the National Health Commission earlier, the recommended Jinhua Qinggan Granule contained the prescription of Shuanghuanglian, lianhua Qingwen granules also contain honeysuckle and Forsythia. "In fact, if weakness is accompanied by fever during the medical observation stage, the above-mentioned proprietary Chinese medicine can be used, which is equivalent to the enhanced version of Shuanghuanglian, " Jin warned, adding that the bitter-cold medicine can easily cause side effects such as diarrhea and abdominal pain, deficiency of the spleen and stomach cold people, the elderly, children or recent poor appetite, diarrhea symptoms of the crowd are not advised to blindly take.
